The idiomatic expression "it takes a lot of balls" means that something requires a great deal of courage, confidence, or bravery. "Having balls" is a slang term for being brave or tough.

However, in the context of golf, "balls" literally refers to the golf balls used to play the game. So when you say, "It takes a lot of balls to golf the way I do," you're humorously implying that your style of golfing is so wild, unconventional, or perhaps even reckless that you lose a lot of golf balls in the process.

The joke works by playing with the literal and figurative meanings of the word "balls," creating a humorous double entendre. It's a witty one-liner that might be appreciated by golf enthusiasts who can relate to the frustrations and challenges of the game.
